4
00:00:14,978 --> 00:00:18,709

5
00:00:19,210 --> 00:00:22,953
<i>巴黎</i>
Paris

6
00:00:48,380 --> 00:00:51,010
我最亲爱的Emile
Emile my dearest one.

7
00:01:31,971 --> 00:01:35,611
[法语]
[speaking french]

8
00:01:35,693 --> 00:01:37,316
是的 夫人
Yes Madame.

9
00:01:46,478 --> 00:01:47,545
我最亲爱的Emile
My dearest Emile,

10
00:01:47,626 --> 00:01:50,544
我丈夫已经改变了计划
my husband has changed his plans.

11
00:01:51,662 --> 00:01:54,608
没有其他的方式说再见
There is no other way to say goodbye.

12
00:01:56,254 --> 00:01:58,778
把我记在你的心中
Remember me in your heart.

13
00:03:03,186 --> 00:03:06,668
<i>12年后</i>
<i>12 Years Later</i>

14
00:03:06,808 --> 00:03:08,539
谁在巴黎出卖了我
Who betrayed me in Paris

15
00:03:08,617 --> 00:03:11,083
为什么你等这么久才来?
and why did you wait so long?

16
00:03:11,157 --> 00:03:13,588
我发现你的贵妇风范令人吃惊
I find your ladyship's attitude surprising.

17
00:03:13,661 --> 00:03:17,342
以上问题的答案与你无关
The answers to those questions are no concern of yours.

18
00:03:17,419 --> 00:03:19,672
我乞求你
On my knees I beg you,

19
00:03:19,749 --> 00:03:21,622
发发慈悲
I employ you to show mercy.

20
00:03:21,698 --> 00:03:24,341
我可不管什么慈悲 夫人
I'm not in the business of mercy Madame.

21
00:03:24,378 --> 00:03:25,353
我没有钱
I haven't the money.

22
00:03:25,390 --> 00:03:26,913
即使我愿意给
Even if I wished

23
00:03:26,950 --> 00:03:29,208
怎么能让我丈夫不发现呢?
how could I without my husband knowing?

24
00:03:29,282 --> 00:03:31,464
连尝试都不去做...这种建议...
Oh you'd be exceedingly ill advised

25
00:03:31,543 --> 00:03:33,096
是个馊主意
not to make an effort.

26
00:03:33,179 --> 00:03:35,010
悉听尊便!
Do your worst.

27
00:03:39,615 --> 00:03:42,355
你别想从我这里得到一个子
You will not have a penny from me,

28
00:03:42,432 --> 00:03:44,300
胆小鬼!
coward!

29
00:04:10,091 --> 00:04:13,982
我的孙子们已经受到了足够的惩罚
My grandsons were punished enough.

30
00:04:15,378 --> 00:04:18,569
我很少收到他们的来信
I hear from them only seldom.

31
00:04:19,206 --> 00:04:22,554
我想他们是不想让我伤心
They wish to spare me their misery I think.

32
00:04:25,050 --> 00:04:29,806
这个魔鬼已经归西了吗?
This monster who brought about their downfall?

33
00:04:29,885 --> 00:04:32,554
他还健在 福尔摩斯先生
He lives and breathes Mr. Holmes

34
00:04:32,634 --> 00:04:35,136
面带笑容
with a smiling face

35
00:04:35,208 --> 00:04:38,343
但内心冷酷无情
and a heart of marble.

36
00:04:38,931 --> 00:04:41,280
你应该早点来找我
You should have come to me sooner.

37
00:04:41,853 --> 00:04:44,606
如果能早点认识你
If only I'd known of you sooner.

38
00:04:44,707 --> 00:04:47,576
我的一个朋友把你介绍给我
A friend gave me your name.

39
00:04:47,732 --> 00:04:49,949
他对你的评价很高
He has a high regard,

40
00:04:50,029 --> 00:04:52,854
就因为你的正义感
for your sense of justice.

41
00:04:53,995 --> 00:04:56,666
你读诗吗?
Do you read poetry?

42
00:05:01,092 --> 00:05:03,140
试试这页
Try a leaf.

43
00:05:08,502 --> 00:05:11,657
C.A.M.魔鬼
CAM devil.

44
00:05:11,737 --> 00:05:15,217
这是我能给你的唯一线索
This is the only clue I can offer you.

45
00:05:15,391 --> 00:05:17,652
或许有用
Maybe it will help.

46
00:05:17,826 --> 00:05:21,505
我不是为了自己 福尔摩斯先生
I wish nothing for myself Mr. Holmes.

47
00:05:21,931 --> 00:05:25,433
那已经太晚了
It is too late for that.

48
00:05:25,828 --> 00:05:28,679
我只希望...
I wish only

49
00:05:29,133 --> 00:05:32,448
能拯救他人
to save others.

50
00:05:43,154 --> 00:05:45,063
3:45去伦敦
3:45 for London.

51
00:05:55,573 --> 00:05:57,755
在那里我觉得很悲哀
I felt great sadness there.

52
00:05:57,834 --> 00:05:59,186
想到那个屋子
To think that that house

53
00:05:59,260 --> 00:06:02,734
回荡着孩子们成长的声音
must have reverberated to the sounds of those boys growing up.

54
00:06:03,227 --> 00:06:05,278
一个掠夺弱者的人
Man who preys upon weakness

55
00:06:05,348 --> 00:06:06,628
面带微笑
with a smiling face

56
00:06:06,706 --> 00:06:08,817
但冷酷无情
and a heart of marble.

57
00:06:15,438 --> 00:06:18,107
一个讹诈专家
A master blackmailer.

58
00:06:18,187 --> 00:06:20,512
我听过人们对他的私语
I've heard whisper of him

59
00:06:20,587 --> 00:06:22,638
但是没人知道他的名字
yet no one has put a name to him.

60
00:06:22,709 --> 00:06:24,262
从没人提及过讹诈之事
Well there's no mention of blackmail.

61
00:06:24,344 --> 00:06:26,941
即使报纸的专栏也没有捕风捉影过
Even a whisper of a newspaper column.

62
00:06:31,268 --> 00:06:33,187
你有记录吗?
You have reported it?

63
00:06:33,912 --> 00:06:36,237
关于她的两个孙子
Of her two grandchildren,

64
00:06:36,312 --> 00:06:39,265
大哥George
George the elder,

65
00:06:39,339 --> 00:06:41,212
和Vike Kroft
and Vike Kroft

66
00:06:41,286 --> 00:06:43,717
被人捉奸
was caught in a moment of indiscretion,

67
00:06:43,792 --> 00:06:46,461
报纸上说是美人计
referred to the paper as the Badger Game.

68
00:06:46,540 --> 00:06:50,111
好像是说这位绅士被妓女勾引上床
It seems to involve a gentleman being lured to the bed of a prostitute

69
00:06:50,193 --> 00:06:51,616
然后被发现
then being discovered

70
00:06:51,689 --> 00:06:53,740
捉奸在床
'In flagrante delicto' by a third party.

71
00:06:53,811 --> 00:06:57,737
像往常一样 这些耸人听闻的报道又弄错了
As usual the sensational press has got it wrong.

72
00:06:57,811 --> 00:06:59,827
那位女士确实是位演员
The lady was an actress that is true

73
00:06:59,899 --> 00:07:01,772
但不是被逮个正着
but it was no [unintelligible]

74
00:07:01,848 --> 00:07:03,263
Hudson太太!
Mrs. Hudson!

75
00:07:03,344 --> 00:07:04,489
他结婚了 福尔摩斯
He was married Holmes

76
00:07:04,526 --> 00:07:06,143
入赘的是全国最有影响力的家族
into one of the highest family's in the land.

77
00:07:06,180 --> 00:07:07,411
报纸上大肆报道了一番
The paper's made plenty of that.

78
00:07:07,448 --> 00:07:08,112
小一点的呢?
And the younger boy?

79
00:07:08,148 --> 00:07:09,644
Edward
Edward.

80
00:07:10,371 --> 00:07:13,075
他为他哥哥报仇
Now, he revenged for his brother,

81
00:07:13,154 --> 00:07:15,229
用左轮枪打了男仆
took a revolver to the footman,

82
00:07:15,311 --> 00:07:18,640
仆人叫...Veitch
who's name was, uh Veitch,

83
00:07:18,721 --> 00:07:19,729
当面开的枪
burst in upon him,

84
00:07:19,799 --> 00:07:21,151
子弹打到了脸上
shot him in the face.

85
00:07:21,225 --> 00:07:22,434
这人还活着
The man lived

86
00:07:22,513 --> 00:07:24,838
但已经毁容了
but was disfigured for life.

87
00:07:24,913 --> 00:07:28,174
审判结束后 他就失踪了
After the trial he disappeared.

88
00:07:28,253 --> 00:07:31,063
必须找到Veitch
It is Veitch we must find

89
00:07:31,141 --> 00:07:33,810
他能带我们找到猎物
to lead us to our prize.

90
00:07:33,889 --> 00:07:35,691
Hudson太太 你不舒服吗?
Ms. Hudson are you not well?

91
00:07:35,767 --> 00:07:36,766
我很好
Of course I'm well.

92
00:07:36,803 --> 00:07:38,625
你知道我讨厌卷心菜的味
Then please you know I hate the smell of cabbage.

93
00:07:38,663 --> 00:07:42,168
兄弟俩肯定受了很多折磨
Surely the brothers would know they're tormenter.

94
00:07:42,239 --> 00:07:46,201
哥哥很丢脸地离开了英国
The older brother fled the country in disgrace.

95
00:07:46,274 --> 00:07:48,680
Edward服刑之后也去找他
Edward joined him having served his sentence,

96
00:07:48,717 --> 00:07:50,030
他们现在在法国某个地方过着富裕的生活
they're now living richly somewhere in France.

97
00:07:50,101 --> 00:07:52,010
再见 Hudson太太
Goodbye Mrs. Hudson.

98
00:07:52,084 --> 00:07:53,637
谢谢
Thank you.

99
00:07:53,719 --> 00:07:56,221
还有一个很奇怪
There is one curiosity.

100
00:08:01,582 --> 00:08:04,879
C.A.M魔鬼
C.A.M Devil.

101
00:08:04,956 --> 00:08:08,191
要是愿意 读读吧 找点线索
Read it for clues if you wish.

102
00:08:09,271 --> 00:08:12,260
我更愿意读Henneson的诗
I rather liked Henneson.

103
00:08:12,332 --> 00:08:13,844
以后再读
But later.

104
00:08:15,741 --> 00:08:19,287
我希望你集中精力
I'd prefer you to direct your energies

105
00:08:19,359 --> 00:08:22,020
看看闲话作家那段
towards the gossip columnists.

106
00:08:24,856 --> 00:08:27,383
草原
The Grasslands.

107
00:08:27,639 --> 00:08:30,261
草原 华生
The Grasslands Watson

108
00:08:31,397 --> 00:08:34,386
毒蛇生活在那里
for which our serpent lies.

109
00:08:40,754 --> 00:08:42,550
告诉我们你要去哪 Charlotte
Do tell us where you're going Charlotte.

110
00:08:42,587 --> 00:08:43,738
说啊
Oh yes do tell.

111
00:08:43,775 --> 00:08:45,280
Lottie你要去哪?
Lottie where are you going?

112
00:08:45,317 --> 00:08:48,198
我可以吗  亲爱的
Shall I, dearest.

113
00:08:48,235 --> 00:08:49,983
说什么?
What's that my love?

114
00:08:50,879 --> 00:08:53,345
要告诉他们我们去哪度蜜月吗?
Tell them where we're going for our honeymoon.

115
00:08:53,418 --> 00:08:55,042
我不反对
I've no objections.

116
00:08:55,123 --> 00:08:57,316
是Buddley Solterton
It's Buddley Solterton.

117
00:09:03,994 --> 00:09:05,452
太浪漫了
How romantic.

118
00:09:05,525 --> 00:09:06,912
是很浪漫
It is actually very.

119
00:09:06,986 --> 00:09:09,579
要是我就去国外什么地方度蜜月
I shall have to choose somewhere abroad for a honeymoon.

120
00:09:09,616 --> 00:09:11,810
巴黎或是罗马
Paris or Rome.

121
00:09:11,892 --> 00:09:12,951
也许吧 Daphne
You may Daphne.

122
00:09:12,988 --> 00:09:15,399
但是要是命中注定要嫁给一个军人
But if one's fate is to marry a soldier,

123
00:09:15,475 --> 00:09:18,285
那她一生就得漂泊异乡了
abroad may well be one's whole life.

124
00:09:18,363 --> 00:09:20,130
你的蜜月呢  Eva小姐?
And your honeymoon Lady Eva?

125
00:09:20,206 --> 00:09:23,052
你和Harry决定了吗?
Have you and Harry decided yet?

126
00:09:23,129 --> 00:09:24,658
佛罗伦萨
Florence,

127
00:09:24,729 --> 00:09:26,745
那不勒斯
Naples,

128
00:09:26,817 --> 00:09:30,221
康斯汀坦布尔 我想吧
Constantinople I think.

129
00:09:30,296 --> 00:09:32,027
听上去不错
Sounds delightful.

130
00:09:32,105 --> 00:09:33,349
你让他嫉妒了
Now you've made him envious.

131
00:09:33,427 --> 00:09:35,823
怎么会
Not at all.

132
00:09:35,897 --> 00:09:37,249
Charlotte 亲爱的
Charlotte my dear,

133
00:09:37,323 --> 00:09:39,125
我得回兵营了
I must return to barracks.

134
00:09:39,201 --> 00:09:40,825
今晚能见到你吗?
Shall I see you this evening?

135
00:09:40,906 --> 00:09:43,610
不行 职责所限
No, duties forbid.

136
00:09:43,690 --> 00:09:46,643
团里有晚宴
Our regimental dinner alas.

137
00:09:54,057 --> 00:09:56,038
女士们 再见
Ladies.

138
00:10:00,493 --> 00:10:02,710
Lottie 他真不错
Lottie he is gorgeous.

139
00:10:02,789 --> 00:10:04,283
也很可爱
He's divine.

140
00:10:04,354 --> 00:10:06,785
你怎么有这福气找到Charlotte呢?
How'd you get so lucky Charlotte?

141
00:10:06,860 --> 00:10:09,006
但是Buddley Solterton在哪?
But where is Buddley Solterton?

142
00:10:09,086 --> 00:10:11,755
真为你高兴 Lottie
Oh I'm so happy for you Lottie.

143
00:12:59,173 --> 00:13:01,426
这是什么?
What is this?

144
00:13:01,505 --> 00:13:04,007
不是出自我的手
It's not in my hand.

145
00:13:04,079 --> 00:13:05,713
亲爱的上校
My dear Colonel

146
00:13:05,920 --> 00:13:09,462
你不会想我把原件给你看吧?
you don't expect me to give you the original do you?

147
00:13:09,500 --> 00:13:11,069
你从哪得到的?
Where did you get this?

148
00:13:11,141 --> 00:13:13,810
谁给你的?
Who gave it to you?

149
00:13:13,889 --> 00:13:15,548
嗯
Oh well,

150
00:13:15,628 --> 00:13:20,704
除了你心爱之人还有谁?
who but the object of your affections.

151
00:13:20,778 --> 00:13:23,624
我不信
I don't believe it.

152
00:13:23,700 --> 00:13:26,297
不可能
It's not possible.

153
00:13:26,379 --> 00:13:27,937
你想从我这儿得到什么?
What do you want from me?

154
00:13:28,014 --> 00:13:29,448
-1200磅! -什么?!
Two hundred pounds! What?

155
00:13:29,485 --> 00:13:32,429
这么点就能搞定一切
For it all to be blown away.

156
00:13:32,466 --> 00:13:34,978
做梦! 一分钱我都不给!
Never! I won't part with a penny.

157
00:13:35,015 --> 00:13:37,332
我要先看着你下地狱
I'll see you in hell first.

158
00:13:37,407 --> 00:13:40,775
想想你可爱的新娘 上校
Think of your lovely bride Colonel.

159
00:13:57,412 --> 00:13:59,265
你对我做了什么?
What have you done to me?

160
00:14:38,533 --> 00:14:39,848
每个人都要问问自己
One has to ask oneself

161
00:14:39,925 --> 00:14:41,795
能吃多少黄油?
how much butter can one eat?

162
00:14:42,707 --> 00:14:44,130
Dotty Martian很明显
Dotty Martian apparently

163
00:14:44,204 --> 00:14:46,185
能吃17勺盐外加一些胡椒粉
got seventeen salt and pepper parts.

164
00:14:46,257 --> 00:14:47,288
17勺?
Seventeen?

165
00:14:47,369 --> 00:14:48,472
是真的
It's true.

166
00:14:48,553 --> 00:14:50,058
我想到了一个解决的办法
I was thinking of a way of dealing with it

167
00:14:50,095 --> 00:14:52,068
-就是... -帮我一下
was to... Help me.

168
00:14:52,105 --> 00:14:53,360
给她写封礼貌的信
Was to mail her politely,

169
00:14:53,397 --> 00:14:58,672
一直都挺有用 直到再也没用
always useful until the awful day when always useless,

170
00:14:58,745 --> 00:15:00,355
她就告诉了公爵夫人
she said to the Duchess.

171
00:15:00,393 --> 00:15:02,361
-不是吧 -是真的
-No. -Yes, it's true.

172
00:15:03,408 --> 00:15:05,869
Lillie无意中听到的 是吧Lillie?
Lillie overheard her didn't you Lillie?

173
00:15:05,947 --> 00:15:08,484
是的 小姐
Yes my lady.

174
00:15:08,557 --> 00:15:11,438
Harry想在海上举行婚礼
Harry wanted us to be married at sea

175
00:15:11,514 --> 00:15:14,087
在一艘私人游船上 只有船员参加
on a pirate ship with only the crew invited

176
00:15:14,158 --> 00:15:15,925
但是谁也不能这样 是吧?
but one really can't can we?

177
00:15:16,001 --> 00:15:17,910
是啊 没人真能那样
No my dear one really can't.

178
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:32,037
我下了一个极愚蠢的赌注
I made an extremely foolish wager

179
00:15:32,109 --> 00:15:35,692
结果最后我和一个重骑兵干上了
but I ended up boxing a dragoon.

180
00:15:42,892 --> 00:15:48,207
这三天里 这场婚礼还有什么要完善的吗?
And will you mend for the nuptials, my dear fellow, in three days?

181
00:15:48,286 --> 00:15:50,918
你还是有点小小的焦虑吧
You have a small flutter in itself.

182
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:53,740
给凉脚丫的厚袜子
Thick socks for cold feet.

183
00:15:53,818 --> 00:15:56,249
要希望它们派不上用场都很难
You can rarely hopes they won't be needed.

184
00:16:12,118 --> 00:16:15,428
是的 我祖父幻想自己是个拳击手
Yeah my grandfather fancied himself as something of a pugilist.

185
00:16:15,465 --> 00:16:17,096
他是个魁梧的人
He was a fortho.

186
00:16:17,133 --> 00:16:19,630
我记得有一年夏天在爱尔兰
I remember one summer in Ireland,

187
00:16:19,701 --> 00:16:22,828
我那时大概有8岁了
I must have been about eight years old I suppose.

188
00:16:22,902 --> 00:16:24,561
他决定给我上一课
He decided to give me a lesson,

189
00:16:24,642 --> 00:16:26,551
我从没有那么害怕过
I've never been so frightened in my life.

190
00:16:26,624 --> 00:16:28,912
Lottie 这是什么?
Lottie what is it?

191
00:16:48,682 --> 00:16:50,105
Lottie?
Lottie?

192
00:16:50,178 --> 00:16:51,672
出什么事了?
What's the problem?

193
00:16:51,743 --> 00:16:54,316
是信...
There's some letters.

194
00:17:04,128 --> 00:17:06,345
什么?
What?

195
00:17:28,063 --> 00:17:31,538
看来去不成Buddley Solterton了
Looks like it's goodbye Buddley Solterton.

196
00:17:31,612 --> 00:17:32,716
我必须去看看她
I must go to her.

