That's not my concern.

588
00:48:31,925 --> 00:48:33,341
小姐 是Dovercourt伯爵
The Earl of Dovercourt my lady.

589
00:48:33,379 --> 00:48:35,443
别紧张 来的是个好人
Don't fuss. Oh there's a good fellow.

590
00:48:36,483 --> 00:48:38,700
Henry
Now Henry.

591
00:48:38,779 --> 00:48:40,277
这位是Milverton先生
This is Mr. Milverton.

592
00:48:42,502 --> 00:48:45,242
很荣幸能结识您 阁下
I'm honored to meet you my Lord.

593
00:48:45,319 --> 00:48:47,892
你在这里干什么?
And what is your business here?

594
00:48:47,964 --> 00:48:51,261
干什么?
Business?

595
00:48:51,339 --> 00:48:53,556
我们要与这位爵爷
Shall we share with his lordship

596
00:48:53,634 --> 00:48:55,685
分享一下我们的小秘密吗 Eva小姐?
our little secret Lady Eva?

597
00:48:55,756 --> 00:48:57,115
不
No.

598
00:48:58,331 --> 00:49:00,406
那就如你所愿
As you wish.

599
00:49:03,863 --> 00:49:05,736
我的名片 先生
My card sir.

600
00:49:05,811 --> 00:49:07,305
谢谢
Thank you.

601
00:49:14,543 --> 00:49:16,796
再见了 两位
Good day at you both.

602
00:49:37,504 --> 00:49:38,369
Stokes?
Stokes?

603
00:49:39,487 --> 00:49:40,396
几点了?
What time is it?

604
00:49:40,433 --> 00:49:41,864
四点过二十
Twenty past four.

605
00:49:43,975 --> 00:49:46,371
还要多久 Escott?
How much longer Escott?

606
00:49:46,446 --> 00:49:50,337
请您原谅我要说的话 Hebworth先生
Well if you'll forgive me for saying so Mr. Hebworth,

607
00:49:50,411 --> 00:49:53,043
你们的管子已经坏得很严重了
you're plumbing's in the shocking stage.

608
00:49:53,125 --> 00:49:55,722
我从没见过这么糟糕的情况
It's the worst I've ever seen.

609
00:50:01,231 --> 00:50:02,899
再给你两天
Two more days

610
00:50:03,115 --> 00:50:04,542
你就滚蛋
then you're out.

611
00:50:16,608 --> 00:50:18,517
今晚来见我
Come and see me tonight.

612
00:50:22,166 --> 00:50:23,457
Aggie
Oh Aggie.

613
00:50:25,020 --> 00:50:26,070
我得到可靠消息
I have it under authority

614
00:50:26,107 --> 00:50:28,811
她每个星期日下午从这里骑马经过
that she rides this way every Sunday afternoon.

615
00:50:28,889 --> 00:50:30,762
你能认出她吗?
Would you recognize her?

616
00:50:30,837 --> 00:50:34,027
我在杂志上见过她
Well I've seen her likeness in a magazine

617
00:50:34,107 --> 00:50:37,784
如果她是和Dovercourt在一起 或许能吧
if she's with Dovercourt, I might.

618
00:50:57,764 --> 00:50:59,116
Eva?
Eva?

619
00:51:00,965 --> 00:51:02,423
马童 勒住马
Boy get the horse.

620
00:51:04,653 --> 00:51:06,384
我是个医生
I'm a Doctor.

621
00:51:06,462 --> 00:51:08,513
她的教母正好住在那边
Her godmother lives just over there.

622
00:51:08,584 --> 00:51:10,512
如果移动是安全的话 我们可以带她过去 医生
We could carry her if it's safe to lift her doctor.

623
00:51:10,549 --> 00:51:12,688
是的 没有受伤 只是晕倒而已
Yes. There's no injury

624
00:51:12,725 --> 00:51:13,801
亲爱的
Darling?

625
00:51:45,253 --> 00:51:46,949
真对不起引来那么大的麻烦
I'm so sorry to be of so much trouble.

626
00:51:47,026 --> 00:51:48,579
你躺在原地别动 亲爱的
You lay where you are my dear.

627
00:51:48,662 --> 00:51:50,571
你现在很安全
You're in safe hands now.

628
00:51:59,586 --> 00:52:01,009
Swinstead女士
Lady Swinstead.

629
00:52:12,110 --> 00:52:17,281
整个英格兰都与您同哀
All England shares in your grief.

630
00:52:17,363 --> 00:52:20,908
我的同事 华生医生 正在为Eva小姐治疗
My colleague, Doctor Watson, is attending Lady Eva.

631
00:52:21,712 --> 00:52:27,515
可怜的孩子 因为我丈夫的死心乱如麻
Poor child is very disturbed by the death of my husband.

632
00:52:27,592 --> 00:52:29,323
没有什么大碍 Swinstead女士
There's nothing serious Lady Swinstead

633
00:52:29,401 --> 00:52:31,239
但是我建议你让她休息一阵
but I would advise you to make her rest

634
00:52:31,314 --> 00:52:32,867
让她自己的医生看看她
and get her own doctor to see her.

635
00:52:32,949 --> 00:52:33,814
当然会的
Of course.

636
00:52:33,888 --> 00:52:35,690
谢谢你 华生医生
Thank you Doctor Watson.

637
00:52:35,767 --> 00:52:38,399
或许Eva小姐需要我为她效劳
May Lady Eva need my services

638
00:52:38,481 --> 00:52:39,783
请收下
please.

639
00:52:46,065 --> 00:52:47,488
Eva?
Eva?

640
00:52:47,560 --> 00:52:50,513
是Milverton让她摔下马的
It was Milverton who caused her fall.

641
00:52:50,587 --> 00:52:52,769
她看见了他的马车
She saw his carriage.

642
00:53:09,269 --> 00:53:11,522
他让他的受害人精神紧张
He rings the nerves of his victims

643
00:53:11,601 --> 00:53:15,206
让自己原本就鼓鼓的钱包更鼓
to add to his already swollen moneybags.

644
00:53:15,289 --> 00:53:18,693
他是伦敦最差劲的男人
He is the worst man in London.

645
00:53:18,767 --> 00:53:22,028
偷鸡摸狗 诡计多端
Seething, slithering and sly.

646
00:53:22,107 --> 00:53:25,242
难道除了留在这里
Yes is there nothing better we can do

647
00:53:25,278 --> 00:53:26,861
我们没有别的可做了吗 福尔摩斯?
than spend our time here Holmes?

648
00:53:26,942 --> 00:53:28,958
你有什么建议吗?
You have any suggestions?

649
00:53:29,030 --> 00:53:31,285
和他对质 讨个说法
Confront him. Challenge him.

650
00:53:31,361 --> 00:53:34,385
先动脑子再动手
The brain before the cudgel rule.

651
00:53:34,458 --> 00:53:35,916
同时
Meanwhile,

652
00:53:35,988 --> 00:53:37,826
他会故伎重演
just like him,

653
00:53:37,902 --> 00:53:39,325
不断勒索他的受害人
he'll squeeze his victims

654
00:53:39,398 --> 00:53:41,379
直到把他们榨干为止
till he's drained them dry

655
00:53:41,450 --> 00:53:45,376
我们却不去阻止他
and we're doing nothing to stop him.

656
00:53:45,452 --> 00:53:47,503
福尔摩斯?
Holmes?

657
00:53:56,201 --> 00:53:59,225
你必须吃饭 孩子
You must eat child.

658
00:54:04,515 --> 00:54:06,946
什么让你烦恼?
What's troubling you?

659
00:54:10,048 --> 00:54:12,680
你在等谁来吗?
Are you expecting someone?

660
00:54:12,761 --> 00:54:15,750
没有
No.

661
00:54:15,823 --> 00:54:19,120
我只是在想我的婚事
I'm just thinking about my wedding.

662
00:54:23,824 --> 00:54:26,670
现在告诉我实话
Now tell me the truth.

663
00:54:54,196 --> 00:54:55,405
抓住你了!
Gotchya?

664
00:55:06,337 --> 00:55:09,910
这房子里的人几点上床 Aggie?
What time do they go to bed in this house Aggie?

665
00:55:09,991 --> 00:55:13,015
你想知道这个干什么?
What do you want to know for?

666
00:55:13,086 --> 00:55:17,427
我就可以知道什么时候来看你是安全的
So I know when it's safe to visit you.

667
00:55:17,505 --> 00:55:20,695
你可以随时到墙边来
You could always come in over the wall.

668
00:55:20,775 --> 00:55:24,665
用小卵石敲我的窗户
Throw pebbles at my window.

669
00:55:24,741 --> 00:55:27,765
哪扇是你的窗?
Which is your window?

670
00:55:27,838 --> 00:55:32,772
如果你娶了我
I'll only tell you

671
00:55:32,847 --> 00:55:34,471
我就告诉你 亲爱的
if you marry me love.

672
00:55:34,551 --> 00:55:36,611
-Aggie 我不能 -那我就不告诉你
-Oh Aggie I can't. -Then I wont tell.

673
00:55:36,648 --> 00:55:39,105
你总是那么牙尖嘴利
You have such a way with words.

674
00:55:40,999 --> 00:55:42,620
好吧
All right.

675
00:55:42,967 --> 00:55:46,686
我在最上面的角落里
I'm at the very, very top on the corner

676
00:55:46,763 --> 00:55:49,123
而主人 他在下面一层
and Master, he's a floor below

677
00:55:49,199 --> 00:55:52,009
但是他靠近花园
but he's next to the garden

678
00:55:52,086 --> 00:55:54,268
Hebworth先生
and Monsieur Hebworth

679
00:55:54,347 --> 00:55:55,935
他在一楼
he's on the ground floor

680
00:55:56,017 --> 00:55:58,377
穿过书房就是
just across from the study.

681
00:55:58,452 --> 00:56:00,669
Lewis睡觉的时候 你来了也吵不醒他
Lewis is sleeping don't you come wake him.

682
00:56:00,748 --> 00:56:02,302
仆人厅里一直流传这个笑话
There's a joke in the servant's hall.

683
00:56:02,339 --> 00:56:04,843
为什么他不睡楼上呢?
Why don't he sleep upstairs?

684
00:56:04,923 --> 00:56:09,478
因为主人想让他看门
Because the master wants him on guard.

685
00:56:14,456 --> 00:56:17,681
他怕夜贼
He's afraid of burglars.

686
00:56:17,761 --> 00:56:20,121
你是夜贼吗?
Are you a burglar?

687
00:56:32,198 --> 00:56:37,345
我被你打动了
You touched my heart.

688
00:56:41,662 --> 00:56:46,454
我会把你当成是我的礼物
I will make you a gift of mine.

689
00:56:58,047 --> 00:56:58,912
出来
Off you go.

690
00:56:58,986 --> 00:57:00,160
出来
Off you go.

691
00:57:03,057 --> 00:57:05,488
Maximilian 谁让你出来的?
Maximilian, who let you out.

692
00:57:05,562 --> 00:57:06,285
停下
Stop.

693
00:57:06,362 --> 00:57:08,088
过来
Come here.

694
00:57:30,574 --> 00:57:33,160
Robert 停下
Robert, Stop it.

695
00:57:43,383 --> 00:57:45,302
停下
Stop it.

696
00:57:57,642 --> 00:57:59,895
我会抓住你的 Escott
I'll get you Escott.

697
00:58:05,157 --> 00:58:07,232
他就在那拐角处
He's just around the corner.

698
00:58:15,802 --> 00:58:18,434
为什么这么大吵大闹?
What's this bloody racket?

699
00:58:18,515 --> 00:58:20,803
是...
Well there...

700
00:58:23,338 --> 00:58:25,459
华生 你会很有兴趣听到下面这个消息
Watson you'll be interested to hear

701
00:58:25,496 --> 00:58:27,588
我订婚了
that I'm engaged to be married.

702
00:58:27,625 --> 00:58:29,006
是吗?
Oh yeah?

703
00:58:31,181 --> 00:58:33,561
和Milverton的女仆
To the Milverton's housemaid.

704
00:58:36,502 --> 00:58:37,533
我的天
Good heavens.

705
00:58:37,616 --> 00:58:39,825
我需要线索
I needed information.

706
00:58:40,921 --> 00:58:43,334
可你做得太过火了
Surely you've gone too far.

707
00:58:44,608 --> 00:58:47,146
这是必不得已
It was a most necessary step.

708
00:58:48,609 --> 00:58:50,553
我和她一起散步
I've walked with her,

709
00:58:50,627 --> 00:58:53,722
和她聊天
talked with her.

710
00:58:53,793 --> 00:58:56,533
天晓得谈了什么
heaven knows talks.

711
00:58:56,611 --> 00:58:57,963
但是这女孩怎么办
But the girl?

712
00:58:58,037 --> 00:59:00,053
没有办法 华生
Can't help it Watson.

713
00:59:00,125 --> 00:59:01,892
在这种赌博下
One must play one's cards as best one can

714
00:59:01,968 --> 00:59:05,063
必须出好每一手牌
when such a stake is on the table.

715
00:59:05,134 --> 00:59:06,901
不过 我很高兴告诉你
However, I rejoice to tell you

716
00:59:06,978 --> 00:59:08,816
我有个讨厌的竞争对手
that I have a hated rival

717
00:59:08,891 --> 00:59:10,206
在我离开的时候
that will cut me out

718
00:59:10,283 --> 00:59:12,223
就会挤掉我的位置
the moment my back is turned.

719
00:59:16,128 --> 00:59:18,239
真是妙不可言的一天
What a splendid day it is.

720
00:59:22,390 --> 00:59:24,441
你喜欢这天气?
You like this weather?

721
00:59:27,713 --> 00:59:29,150
她来了
She's here.

722
00:59:33,731 --> 00:59:36,720
我父亲在我十二岁的时候过世了
My father died when I was 12.

723
00:59:36,792 --> 00:59:38,843
我母亲留在这个国家里
My mother stays in the country.

724
00:59:38,915 --> 00:59:40,409
Swinstead阁下和夫人
Lord and Lady Swinstead

725
00:59:40,480 --> 00:59:41,974
让我在伦敦有家的感觉
have made London home to me

726
00:59:42,046 --> 00:59:45,723
去年安排我参加了社交季
but indeed they arranged my season last year.

727
00:59:45,803 --> 00:59:47,427
给我你的手套
Give me your gloves.

728
00:59:51,614 --> 00:59:52,717
Hudson太太
Oh Mrs. Hudson,

729
00:59:52,796 --> 00:59:54,384
你这是在干什么?
what do you think you're doing?

730
00:59:54,466 --> 00:59:56,410
整个早上你都没有出门 福尔摩斯先生
You haven't been out this morning Mr. Holmes

731
00:59:56,484 --> 00:59:59,506
不做一个侦探 也能看这位年轻女士
and you don't have to be a detective to see that this young lady

732
00:59:59,581 --> 01:00:01,692
大病初愈
is recently up from a sick bed.

733
01:00:01,772 --> 01:00:04,547
不是吗 亲爱的?
Isn't that so my dear?

734
01:00:04,625 --> 01:00:07,720
我们必须让她的脸颊重现红润
We must put some roses back in those cheeks.

735
01:00:07,790 --> 01:00:08,893
谢谢
Thank you.

736
01:00:08,974 --> 01:00:10,812
一碗热汤真是个好主意
The broth is an excellent idea.

737
01:00:10,887 --> 01:00:12,903
Hudson太太 请离开一下好吗?
Mrs. Hudson will you vanish?

738
01:00:21,080 --> 01:00:22,953
我说了离开
I said vanish.

739
01:00:26,995 --> 01:00:29,018
他是我的初恋
He was my first love.

740
01:00:30,299 --> 01:00:34,746
在Suffick我们邻居家的儿子
The son of some neighbors of ours in Suffick

741
01:00:34,822 --> 01:00:37,811
但是我们门不当户不对
but we were ill matched.

742
01:00:37,883 --> 01:00:40,872
他没有什么前途
He had few prospects.

743
01:00:40,946 --> 01:00:43,057
当我来到伦敦
When I came down to London

744
01:00:43,137 --> 01:00:44,346
参加去年的社交季
Iast year for the season

745
01:00:44,424 --> 01:00:47,056
我便和他分手了
I broke off with him.

746
01:00:47,138 --> 01:00:51,764
我没有意识到自己让他有多伤心
I didn't realize how much I hurt him.

747
01:00:51,834 --> 01:00:53,945
他退回了我的信
He returned my letters

748
01:00:54,026 --> 01:00:55,484
我把它们放进了箱子
and I put them away in a trunk,

749
01:00:55,557 --> 01:00:56,941
一直保管着
which I keep with me.

750
01:00:58,931 --> 01:01:02,370
那些信写了什么?
Now the substance of these letters?

751
01:01:06,029 --> 01:01:07,617
一些蠢话
They're just a little foolish.

752
01:01:07,699 --> 01:01:10,889
却足够引起你未婚夫的怀疑?
But sufficient to cause your fiance misgiving?

753
01:01:13,613 --> 01:01:17,681
Harry如此为我骄傲
Harry's so proud of me.

754
01:01:17,753 --> 01:01:19,662
有时我真害怕
It frightens me sometimes

755
01:01:19,735 --> 01:01:23,957
如果自己辜负了他的期望
that I cannot live up to his expectation of me.

756
01:01:26,416 --> 01:01:28,704
是你的侍女发现的信吗?
Was it your maid who found these letters?

757
01:01:28,781 --> 01:01:31,556
是Lillie 是的
Lillie yes.

758
01:01:31,634 --> 01:01:33,452
我相信过她
I trusted her.

759
01:01:35,461 --> 01:01:36,662
我不敢相信
I cannot believe

760
01:01:36,698 --> 01:01:39,116
她会这样背叛我
she could have betrayed me like this.

761
01:01:42,106 --> 01:01:45,575
这个 Lillie怎么会知道Milverton?
How would this Lillie know about Milverton?

762
01:01:45,612 --> 01:01:52,083
我想她之所以会想到这个主意
I think the idea may have come to her

763
01:01:52,160 --> 01:01:56,673
是因为之前发生在我朋友身上的不幸
through a misfortune that befell a friend of mine,

764
01:01:56,753 --> 01:02:03,360
Charlotte 她原本要结婚
Charlotte, who was to have married

765
01:02:03,432 --> 01:02:05,305
嫁给Dorking上校
a Colonel Dorking.

766
01:02:20,722 --> 01:02:26,488
Milverton先生给她寄去了些信
And Mr. Milverton sent her some letters.

767
01:02:26,567 --> 01:02:28,959
都是些让人痛苦的信
They were very distressing.

768
01:02:31,383 --> 01:02:35,401
当她收到信时 Lillie和我都在场
Lillie and I were there when she received them.

769
01:02:39,335 --> 01:02:42,324
没想到同样的命运会降临到我身上
To think the same fate has befallen me.

770
01:02:42,397 --> 01:02:44,970
一切都会过去的 Eva小姐
It will be all right Lady Eva.

771
01:02:45,041 --> 01:02:47,329
你能做什么呢?
What could you do?

772
01:02:47,406 --> 01:02:50,703
我的婚礼在18日
My marriage is on the 18th.

773
01:02:53,042 --> 01:02:55,295
他提出要求
He's demanding that

774
01:02:55,373 --> 01:02:58,042
要在婚礼前四天
the money be paid to him

775
01:02:58,121 --> 01:03:01,631
也就是14日付钱给他
four days prior to the wedding on the 14th,

776
01:03:01,705 --> 01:03:03,436
在舞会那天
on the day of the dance.

777
01:03:03,514 --> 01:03:05,043
舞会?
Dance?

778
01:03:05,114 --> 01:03:08,518
Dovercourt阁下安排了一次婚宴
Lord Dovercourt has arranged a wedding feast

779
01:03:08,593 --> 01:03:11,510
邀请了伦敦一半的人
and invited half of London.

780
01:03:15,273 --> 01:03:18,119
我担心死了
I'm dreading it.

781
01:03:18,195 --> 01:03:21,492
如果你愿意让我全权代理
If you will place yourself in my hands

782
01:03:21,570 --> 01:03:23,194
